<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to King <persName corresp="#p_FI1" type="to">Farouk</persName> of Egypt</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d149fn1">Sent by the Advanced Liaison Group, Allied Force
                                Headquarters, North Africa, to the Headquarters, United States Army
                                Forces in the Middle East, Cairo, as message 952, which was marked
                                as being from <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, for
                                the eyes of <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">Kirk</persName> alone, and
                                began “Please deliver the following to His Majesty the King”.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">Kirk</persName> forwarded the
                                message to the King via <persName corresp="#p_HSAP1">Hassanayn</persName> on November 21, 1943.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-20">20 November 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>On landing in French North Africa I have just heard of your motor
                                accident.<note n="2" xml:id="d149fn2">See <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName>’s telegram of November 18, 1943, to <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_97">p. 97</ref>.</note> I am deeply
                            sorry and hope to see you when I am in Egypt.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RFD1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D.
                                        Roosevelt</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>